      "writtenOn": "2019-08-02T05:33:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let us establish consistent terms about parametric tests and define them here. Particularly we want names of (1) tests with variants and (2) test variant instances. Currently (1) is not explicitly defined, and we use inconsistent terms for (2) (\"variations of the test\", \"param case\", etc.)\n\nI think we want to name (1) \"parametric tests\". I don\u0027t have strong opinion about (2) but maybe \"test variants\"?\n\nFor example:\n\n A test is called *parametric* if Params is set in its metadata. Each entry in Params defines a *test variant*.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "7205ba16fb57fb13bbb819a2b133dc1676e8abe0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
