      "message": "I see you use the term \"param case\" to describe a variant of a parametric test, but I\u0027m not very confortable with use of \"param\" as a word because it\u0027s not clear what is its full wording.\n\nI guess it is \"parametric case\", but I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s a natural wording. https://www.google.com/search?hl\u003den\u0026gl\u003dus\u0026q\u003d\"parametric+case\"\n\nHow about \"test parameter\" or \"test variant\"?",
